               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra, name of the archangel Mikaʾel in Texts I and II, name of the donor (fol. 11va); elements of the punctuation signs and of the text dividers; elements of Ethiopic numerals.&#xD;
Two lines on the incipit page of Text I; two initial lines of Texts I-3, first word of Text I-4; first word of subsections of Text I-1; two initial lines of subsections of Texts I-2 and II (miracles); a few initial words in the incipit of a subsection of Text I-4; first word or first letters of each strophe of Text I-5.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>Some miracles in Text I-2 are followed by an ʾarke-hymn:</note>
                     <note>- ለዘዘነብር፡ መነኮስ፡ በደሴተ፡ ጤግሮስ፡ ፈለግ። … (fol. 48vb)</note>
                     <note>- ለፊላታዎስ፡ ኤጲስ፡ ቆጶስ፡ ሰሚረኪ፡ ጽድቆ። … (fol. 51rb-va)</note>
                     <note>- ከመ፡ ጸሐፈ፡ ደቅስዮስ፡ ተአምረኪ፡ እሉደ። … (fol. 52ra)</note>
                     <note>- ብእሲ፡ አረማዊ፡ ኀበ፡ ሥዕልኪ፡ ተሪቦ። … (fol. 53rb-va)</note>
                     <note>- መበለት፡ ሠናይት፡ ጊዜ፡ ትጸሊ፡ ጸሎተ። … (fol. 54vb-55ra)</note>
                     <note>- ግርማ፡ ተአምሪኪ፡ እግዝእትየ፡ ጥቀ፡ ይበድር፡ ፍጥና። … (fol. 56rb)</note>
                     <note>- ሰሚዖ፡ ሕፃን፡ ለእሙ፡ ገዓራ። … (fol. 59ra-b)</note>
                     <note>- ብእሲ፡ አረማዊ፡ መዝገበ፡ ዓመፃ፡ ወእከይ። … (fol. 66vb)</note>
                     <note>- እምድኅረ፡ ሞተት፡ ወለት፡ ዘትሰመይ፡ ዲና። … (fol. 70vb)</note>
                     <note>Text I-4 includes the hymns:</note>
                     <note>- ʾO-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl bä-kǝlʾe Maryam wäladitä ʾamlak ʾǝmmu lä-ʾǝgziʾǝnä ʾIyäsus Krǝstos kähali … “O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Godbearing, Mother of our Lord Jesus Christ the Almighty …” (fol. 10vb, l. 4-19)</note>
                     <note>- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾǝgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl bä-kǝlʾe Maryam wäladitä ʾamlak ʾǝmmä bǝrhan ʾǝmmä qwǝrban … “Salutation to you, o my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, Goldbearing, Mother of the Light, Mother of the Eucharist…” (fols. 10vb, l. 19-11ra)</note>
                     <note>Text I-5 comprises 32 strophes, which are strophes 1-31, 33 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-51.</note>
